A year ago I met Cindy. She was found on a construction sight, (by the beautiful @valrosecuriel) and had clearly been abused by her previous owners. She was very skittish and scared, particularly around men, including me. So I was fostering her, looking for an owner to give her all the love she deserved. But until I found someone, I wanted us to get along. Someone told me it would help her if I let her sleep in bed with me. So I did. The next morning it was like waking up to a different dog, it was as if she finally knew I wasnâ€™t going to kill her, and she pushed her face against mine... Some people got in contact and asked to meet her... and I said no. Me and Cindy were in love, and there was nothing either of us could do about it. And it has been such a joy, taking care of her and having her excited face to come home to. Dogs nail it, donâ€™t they? They greet you with such enthusiasm whether youâ€™ve been gone for a month or half an hour. Thatâ€™s why I write her name in my gratitude journal every day. Cindy. Love her.
Sheer socks are in, and I donâ€™t care what anyone has to say about it.
